First Italian cities ' Sept CPI data out on Sept 23 . Preliminary consumer price inflation data for September from Milan and Bologna , the first of the 10 sample Italian cities to report , will be published on September 23 , the two cities said . On Monday September 16 national statistics office ISTAT is due to issue the complete calendar for all the cities ' CPI data . ISTAT will issue the final national figures on October 4 . The annual rate of inflation fell in August to 3 . 4 percent , the lowest for 27 years . This followed a 3 . 6 percent CPI rise in July and was the seventh successive drop . - - Milan newsroom + 392 66129589 
